  "description": [
    "STATE PRESS Page Four They We Never Learn By S S Taylor Associate Editor A science fiction TV drama tells how a doctor transferred his knowledges and skills to the brain of a patient who then carried on the doctors dreain of research Such a surgical transfer of knowledge would be marvelous indeed But it would be nowhere near as marvelous as mans failure to learn by experience The accumulated wisdom of the ages is his for the taking but does he take it No some of the outstanding tendencies of life in the present day repeat outstanding errors of the past One of these errors is illustrated In the current denunci ations of the NAACP by many segregationists Many of these seem to think that the NAACP is the cause of the fight a gainst segregation and therefore to stop integration it is only necessary to stop or discredit the NAACP all it outsider radical communist inspired 1 This is a survival of the old old technique so familiar to the elders among us silence the leader Thruout slavery and thru the early stages of freedom there wen those who attempted to keep the Negro subservien by indentifying isolating"
